Executive Profile
Thomas D. Christopoul  Executive Chairman, GPS Industries, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships52--
Background

		Mr. Thomas D. Christopoul, also known as Tom, serves as the Chief Executive Officer at GPSi Holdings. Mr. Christopoul founded Somerset Shore Associates, Inc. in 2005 and serves as its President. He serves as Senior Managing Director at Guggenheim Partners, where he leads the operation of the Real Estate and Infrastructure investments of on a global basis. He has extensive international experience, having negotiated large scale outsource, joint venture and partnership ... deals throughout Western and Eastern Europe, Canada, Mexico, Central and South America, Australia, South Africa, Thailand, China and Japan. He was a Senior Partner at Cain Hoy Enterprises. Mr. Christopoul served as Operating Partner since 2009 and Senior Advisor of Falconhead Capital, LLC from September 2009 through April 2013. He served as the Executive Chairman and Interim Chief Executive Officer at Rita's Water Ice Franchise Company, LLC. Mr. Christopoul served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Resources Global Professionals, Inc, where he also served as an Independent Director on Resources’ board as Chairman of the Corporate Governance. He has advised several global private investment firms on acquisitions, divestments and turnarounds of companies ranging in size to several billion dollars in revenue. From January 30, 2006 to 2009, he served as a member of the Board of Directors and also served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Resources Connections, Inc. Mr. Christopoul served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Resources Connection Inc. from June 2008 to July 23, 2009. He was also Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Advance-Ross Industries. He led the sale of that unit to Chartwell Investments in 2004. He served as the Co-Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Marketing Services Division of Avis Budget Group, Inc. (Formerly Cendant Corp.) since October 2003. Mr. Christopoul worked at Cendant for more than 10 years. He managed and integrated the Cendant’s three direct marketing units and before retiring from Cendant in the fall of 2005, he led the strategic divestment of that division in a sale to private equity firm Apollo Management, LP. He also managed the company’s corporate aviation department. He served as the Founder and Chairman of the Cendant Charitable Foundation. He served as Senior Executive Vice President of Avis Budget Group, Inc. since April 2000. From April 2000 to October 2003, he served as Chief Administrative Officer of Avis Budget Group, Inc. From January 2000 to April 2000, he served as President of Cendant Membership Services. From October 1999 to January 2000, Mr. Christopoul served as an Executive Vice President of Corporate Services of Avis Budget Group, Inc. From April 1998 to October 1999, he served as an Executive Vice President of Human Resources for Avis Budget Group, Inc. and from December 1997 to April 1998, served as its Senior Vice President of Human Resources. Mr. Christopoul served as Senior Vice President of Human Resources for HFS from October 1996 to December 1997 and its Vice President of Human Resources from October 1995 to October 1996. He led worldwide human resources and information technology, marketing and a broad array of corporate staff functions on a global basis through his service in a number of senior executive positions, including Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of the Financial Services Division of Cendant for 10 years, where he managed Jackson-Hewitt Tax Services as Senior Executive Vice President and Chief Administrative Officer, Executive Vice President of Corporate Services, Senior Vice President of Human Resources. In June 2004, he led the 100 percent Initial Public Offering of Jackson-Hewitt Tax Services. As the Senior Executive Vice President and Chief Administrative Officer at Cendant, he led several corporate functions of Cendant on a global basis. He served as the Director of Labor Relations for the Nabisco Biscuit Company and also worked for several years at the Pepsi-Cola Company. He serves as the Non-Executive Chairman of Hudson Crossing, LLC. He serves as the Executive Chairman of GPS Industries, LLC and GPS Industries Inc. He has been a Director of Resources Global Professionals, Inc., since January 30, 2006. He has been an Independent Director of Rexnord Corporation since February 26, 2013. He serves as a Director of TAI, Inc. and Cabana Cachaca, LLC. He serves as a member of the Board of Directors of several privately held companies. He has been an Independent Director of Apollo Residential Mortgage, Inc. since July 2011. Mr. Christopoul was a Director of SBE Entertainment Group, LLC. He served as a Director at Nor1, Inc. He served as the Vice Chairman of the Board of Pinnacle Care International. He served as an Independent Director of Resources Connection Inc. from January 26, 2006 to July 23, 2009. He served as a Director of Jackson Hewitt Tax Service Inc. since February 2004. Mr. Christopoul holds an M.S. from Purdue University where he is a distinguished alumnus and a B.A. degree from Rutgers University.Read Full Background




